page.title: 07HISTORY OF FRETTENHAM
page.content: We interviewied eight people about the history of{Frettenham.}Only two of these were born there. Hardly anyone could tell us any history. One interviewee told us that from an aircraft you can see part of a Roman road. Boadicea camped on a piece of land now used for horse grazing near Buxton road . {The Rose and Crown}public house got its name from a plaque of the rose of England. Henry VIII had refreshments there on his way to see Anne Boleyn at{Blickling Hall. Most people have not been living in the village all their life, but some people have. One person has lived in{Frettenham}for fifty one years and knows a lot about Frettenham,his name is Mr.Fisher.
